  <brief_title>Low-dose Peg-interferon Plus Ribavirin (IFN/RBV) for Prevention of Hepatocellular Carcinoma (HCC) Recurrence in Patients Who Had Surgery to Remove Primary HCC</brief_title>
  <official_title>Phase 4 Study of Peg-interferon Plus Ribavirin Therapy for Prevention of Hepatocellular Carcinoma</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Kyoto University</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Kyoto University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether low-dose peg-interferon plus ribavirin
      therapy is effective in the prevention of hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) in patients who had
      the curative resection of primary HCC.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
